	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Dec 17th 4:33 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=27875><span id=Scholar>psmongin</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>127 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.58]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>There are some FAR better bows for the purposes you mentioned than this, or pretty much any high end Velious bow.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>The top end player-crafted will have significantly more range than this, and if you are pulling, ratio isn't important at all.  If you are FD pulling from an arrow shot, you won't shoot more than once, you'll drop and do your FD pull, so being able to shoot quickly is irrelevant.  High damage is nice, but truly not necessary when your talking any levels above the mid-level range.  Pulling a mob with 5k with a 40 point shot or a 60 point shot won't appreciably decrease your combat time.<br><br>Basically, for less money and effort, an SK, Pally, or Warrior can get a far better bow for pulling purposes.<br><br>Ranger's are the only class that truly can use Archery as a viable method of damage in the post-50 game, and that is solely due to the Trueshot discipline.  Before you get upset when someone suggests that a bow be Ranger only, keep in mind that for most of these bows, Rangers are the only class that will find applicable use out of them.<br><br>I'm personally against restricting a tag on an item like this for solely Rangers, but frankly, Rangers are the only ones who will see a benefit out of this bow, or pretty much any of the other high end bows.</p>&nbsp;<br>Malevant Faeshadow.&nbsp;&nbsp;Outrider.</td></td></tr>
